<!-- intro slide two -->
<h1 class="big-text text-center" id="intro-2" style="display:none">SNAP, or Food Stamps, are available to individuals and families with income below 130 percent of the poverty line. <br>
  <i class="fa fa-sort-desc" id="intro-2"></i>
</h1>

<!-- intro slide three -->
<h1 class="big-text text-center" id="intro-3" style="display:none">In November 2013, SNAP households saw a cut in benefits after the American Recovery and Reinvestment Act of 2009's boost to the program ended. <br>
  <i class="fa fa-sort-desc" id="intro-3"></i>
</h1>

<!-- intro slide four -->
<h1 class="big-text text-center" id="intro-4" style="display:none">Months later, the 2014 Farm Bill was signed into law, cutting $8.7 billion from the program over the next 10 years.<br>
  <i class="fa fa-sort-desc" id="intro-4"></i>
</h1>

